                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "In Python, it is possible to overwrite any method of any object if you really want to.  But IPython exposes a few 'hooks', methods which are *designed* to be overwritten by users for customization purposes.  This module defines the default versions of all such hooks, which get used by IPython if not overridden by the user."
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
